HEADWORD: Wasteweir
<hw>Waste"weir`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An overfall, or
weir, for the escape, or overflow, of superfluous water from a canal,
reservoir, pond, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wasting</ent>⟦br⟧
